     \cf15 \cb16  157 +\cf13 1. **Precipitation as a multiplier, not an additive component.\cf3 \cb1 \
     \cf15 \cb16      +\cf13 ** Rain can destroy an otherwise good score regardless of dept\cf3 \cb1 \
     \cf15 \cb16      +\cf13 h or snowfall \'97 a 0.2 multiplier for heavy rain is intentional\cf3 \cb1 \
     \cf15 \cb16      +\cf13  and reflects real conditions.                                \cf3 \cb1 \
     \cf15 \cb16  158 +\cf13                                                               \cf3 \cb1 \
     \cf15 \cb16  159 +\cf13 2. **72-hour snowfall window.** Used consistently across both \cf3 \cb1 \
     \cf15 \cb16      +\cf13 the fresh snowfall score and the thin-base rescue clause (>= 8\cf3 \cb1 \
     \cf15 \cb16      +\cf13 " in 72hrs rescues a sub-24" base to 0.2).                    \cf3 \cb1 \
     \cf15 \cb16  160 +\cf13                                                               \cf3 \cb1 \
     \cf15 \cb16  161 +\cf13 3. **Piecewise linear interpolation.** Rather than hard step f\cf3 \cb1 \
     \cf15 \cb16      +\cf13 unctions between breakpoints, scores interpolate continuously \cf3 \cb1 \
     \cf15 \cb16      +\cf13 within each band. This avoids discontinuous jumps (e.g., a res\cf3 \cb1 \
     \cf15 \cb16      +\cf13 ort at 35" scoring identically to one at 30").                \cf3 \cb1 \
     \cf15 \cb16  162 +\cf13                                                               \cf3 \cb1 \
     \cf15 \cb16  163 +\cf13 4. **Precipitation type derived from temperature + snowfall ra\cf3 \cb1 \
     \cf15 \cb16      +\cf13 te.** Rather than relying on a separate "precip type" API fiel\cf3 \cb1 \
     \cf15 \cb16      +\cf13 d, we classify using: temp < 30\'b0F \uc0\u8594  snow; temp 30\'9634\'b0F \u8594  mixed\cf3 \cb1 \
     \cf15 \cb16      +\cf13  (unless snowfall_mm_hr > 5, then snow override); temp > 34\'b0F \cf3 \cb1 \
     \cf15 \cb16      +\cf13 \uc0\u8594  rain.                                                       \cf3 \cb1 \
     \cf15 \cb16  164 +\cf13                                                               \cf3 \cb1 \
     \cf15 \cb16  165 +\cf13 5. **Ability-weighted composite.** Experts weight fresh snowfa\cf3 \cb1 \
     \cf15 \cb16      +\cf13 ll (0.40) much higher than base depth (0.30). Beginners revers\cf3 \cb1 \
     \cf15 \cb16      +\cf13 e this (depth 0.45, snowfall 0.15) because they rely on groome\cf3 \cb1 \
