\f1\b Key design decisions to be aware of
\f0\b0                                            \
                                                            \
  - \cf10 ski_date\cf3  is the 
\f1\b first ski day
\f0\b0 , not arrival date. If the user arrives the\
  night before, the caller adds 1 day.                                          \
  - \cf10 wind_mph\cf3  and \cf10 temp_f\cf3  use 
\f1\b step functions
\f0\b0  (flat value per band), not smooth\
  interpolation \'97 this is intentional per spec.                                 \
  - \cf10 precip_mm_hr\cf3  acts as a 
\f1\b multiplier
\f0\b0  (0.2\'961.0) on the final weather score, not\
  an additive component. Heavy rain can collapse an otherwise high score        \
  regardless of depth.                                      \
  - Weather is queried at 
\f1\b base lodge coordinates
\f0\b0 . This is a known limitation \'97  \
  upper mountain conditions may be better than the score suggests.              \
  - The API uses \cf10 past_days = 3\cf3  + \cf10 forecast_days = 10\cf3 , so \cf10 ski_date\cf3  must be within\
  today + 10 days.                                                              \
